name: Collins,Samuel
bio: ^Summary:^ Samuel Collins is a former Tier-1 Specialist and highly volatile hostile asset. Collins originally served in the USMC alongside Founder Rodriguez prior to Rodriguez's transfer to the Navy SEALs. The two were reunited when Collins was selected for UEJTF Team 11 (OP-UE). His inclusion was based on extreme physical agility and a highly recognized, aggressive determination—intel noted that once assigned an objective, Collins possessed a near-pathological drive to complete it. ^Psychological Profile & Radicalization:^ During OP-UE, Collins began exhibiting severe |anti-establishment paranoia|. Intelligence intercepts from his time on Team 11 show a growing delusion that global governments and NATO command were inherently corrupt. Despite his physical capabilities, official UEJTF command reports (submitted by team leadership) downgraded his performance to "Adequate," citing a severe lack of discipline and deteriorating team cohesion. Collins developed a specific, unsubstantiated fixation on Founder Rodriguez, accusing him of manipulating task force objectives. The Mutiny (2031): When NATO officially suspended the investigation into the target known as "Ash", Collins fully radicalized. Bypassing the chain of command, he illegally mobilized a splinter cell of operators he deemed "trustworthy" to conduct an unsanctioned, rogue hunt for the target. This mutiny directly led to the catastrophic facility explosion in Kazakhstan. ^TRANSCRIPT LOG: NATO JOINT MILITARY TRIBUNAL [CLASSIFIED]^ *DATE: 14 NOV 2031* *SUBJECT: COLLINS, SAMUEL. MSGT, USMC / UEJTF TEAM 11* %PRESIDING: COLONEL T. HARRINGTON (JAG), MAJOR M. NOVAK (LIAISON)* *[RECORDING COMMENCES]* *COL. HARRINGTON:* Master Sergeant Collins, you have waived your right to preliminary counsel. I will state for the record that this board finds your decision highly ill-advised given the severity of the charges. *MSGT. COLLINS:* Read them, Colonel. Let’s get it over with. *COL. HARRINGTON:* Very well. You are formally charged under the Uniform Code of Military Justice with the following: Article 92, Disobeying a direct order from a superior commissioned officer. Article 121, Larceny of military property, specifically Class-V ordnance and transport vehicles. Article 134, Endangerment of a non-combatant... *MSGT. COLLINS:* (Interrupting) I didn’t endanger the kid. I pulled him out of the blast radius. *COL. HARRINGTON:* Master Sergeant, Captain Rodriguez’s official After-Action Report explicitly states you utilized the local national, Nirvan Shwani, as human cover to secure your own extraction during the Rozhia engagement. *MSGT. COLLINS:* Rodriguez is a liar. He wasn't even in the blast zone. *COL. HARRINGTON:* Captain Rodriguez’s combat record is immaculate, Collins. Yours, currently, reads like a psychological break. Which brings us to the most severe charge. Article 119, Manslaughter. Through gross negligence and unauthorized deployment to the Kazakhstan border, you directly caused the deaths of three NATO operatives: Specialist ||"Libra"||, Staff Sergeant Gavalas, and Contractor Seale. *MSGT. COLLINS:* We found the development site. Ash was there. They were building the core—||a bio-weapon, ENTICORE||. Hugh knew it. He let those men die to bury the evidence. *COL. HARRINGTON:* (Sighs audibly) Master Sergeant... Allied Intelligence swept the Kazakhstan blast crater. It was an abandoned Soviet-era refinery. There was no ||bio-weapon||. There was no research facility. There was only you, stealing a vacuum bomb and dropping a concrete ceiling on your own team. *MSGT. COLLINS:* (Silence. Audio picks up shifting chains) *COL. HARRINGTON:* Your commanding officer requested leniency, citing severe combat fatigue. That is the only reason the prosecution is not seeking a life sentence at Leavenworth. *MSGT. COLLINS:* Hugh asked for leniency. Of course he did. He needs me alive to know he won. *MAJOR NOVAK:* Sam. Shut up. Take the deal. *MSGT. COLLINS:* (Pause) Three years in Marshall. That’s the deal? *MAJOR NOVAK:* Yes. *MSGT. COLLINS:* You read the file, Major? *MAJOR NOVAK:* I read the file. *MSGT. COLLINS:* Then you know what he is. (To the board) |I plead guilty. Lock me up.| But when he turns whatever he found in that 'empty' crater on you... don't say nobody warned you. *[RECORDING TERMINATED]* Current Status: Court-martialed for insubordination, theft of military assets, and extreme negligence, Collins served three years in Marshall Prison. He now resides in NewLake City under a civilian cover. Collins is considered a Level 5 Threat; he remains a highly capable, radicalized operator who still harbors his UETF-era delusions regarding Founder Varga and ECAF.

name: Rodriguez,Houston
seen:
First Seen: 2031, Operation Unknown Entity (Team 11 Lead).
Last Seen: 2047, Exfiltrating Entity Corp HQ via private VTOL.
gear:
Tactical Preference: Sterile kits. He avoids the "3-line" branding used by his subordinates, preferring bespoke, unbranded high-tier ballistic protection.

The "Will" Inscription: Intelligence suggests Rodriguez carries a |customized .45 ACP sidearm| with internal engravings dedicated to ||his brother.||
bio:
*Summary:*
Rodriguez is the primary architect of the current global security landscape. Following a decorated tenure in the USMC and Navy SEALs, his trajectory shifted violently after the Ukraine Incident. ||The confirmed arrival of his brother, Will, in Ukraine|| for treatment and his subsequent "disappearance" served as the catalyst for Rodriguez’s disillusionment with NATO’s bureaucratic limitations.

*Psychological Profile:*
Exhibits |"Clinical Detachment."| He is noted for his "surgical" approach to high-intensity conflict, a trait first recognized by Major Marcus Novak. Rodriguez no longer views conflict as a matter of ideology, but as a series of logistics and leverage. He is the ghost in the machine of the ENTICORE development, using his grief for his brother to fuel a global hunt for the "Architects" of the medical disappearance.

name: Serrey, Cham
bio:
*Summary:*
Cham Serrey is the foundation of the modern ghost weapon and explosive smuggling network. Operating out of Cambodia—a country characterized by a central alluvial plain surrounded by dense, heavily forested mountains like the Cardamom range—Serrey utilized a legitimate flour distribution company |(JJH2+X2R) pinpoint the Kaopisat Group's central compound| as a front for (TKG). His network was responsible for the global distribution of firearms, hard plastic/fibre ghost weapons, and the highly volatile "Ni-Redundant" explosives.

*May 29th (2031):*
At 0300 AM, the UETF executed a coordinated raid on suspected TKG hideouts (JJH2+X2R) pinpoint the Kaopisat Group's central compound to arrest Serrey and secure evidence. While Serrey successfully evaded the strike teams, the operation resulted in a catastrophic loss of inventory for TKG, with massive caches of weaponized metal tubes found disguised within flour shipments. Despite his escape and the lack of concrete evidence to finalize his arrest warrant, the raid effectively dismantled his regional monopoly. He is known to be a high-ranking administrator on the digital "Silk Route" bidding network.
